            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Office of<lb/>
                L. E. FRIDENBERG&#44;<lb/>
                IMPORTER OF<lb/>
                DIAMONDS<lb/>
                WATCHES AND FINE JEWELRY&#44;<lb/>
                NO. 936 ARCH STREET&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; Sept. 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1878<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>Will you be kind enough<lb/> to furnish me with a (brief&#41; written<lb/> answer upon the following points.<lb/> 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>. Did Maimonides&#44; at any time<lb/> of his life&#44; profess Mohammedanism.<lb/> 2d. What is the true story of his &#34;excommu&#45;<lb/>nication.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>3d. In what estimation was he held by<lb/> <sic>cotemporary</sic> Judaism.  In what estimation<lb/> is he held by modern orthodox Judaism.<lb/>  4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> What was the true nature of his views<lb/> upon creation&#59; immortality etc. Were they<lb/> what is called &#34;Averroism&#91;&#63;&#93;.&#34;  What is their<lb/> relation to the Mosaic teachings.<lb/></p>
            <p>I desire to communicate your<lb/> answer to a Christian friend with<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>whom I have a discussion&#59; and<lb/> therefore a note <hi rend="underline">at your convenience</hi><lb/> will greatly oblige<lb/></p>
            <p>Very Respectfully Yours<lb/>
                S. Solis Cohen<lb/>
                1229 Franklin St.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
